node.text: Mental illness, depression, and anxiety look different on everyone. Check on your people's regards of how “put together” they may seem. Remember that even if people don’t seem to be in distress on the outside, believe them, if they say they are. 📷@punkmom_

node.text:
Drop three ♥♥♥ in the comments if you can relate!⁠
⁠
Here's a post that I think a lot of people will appreciate: phrases or sentences that we 𝘴𝘩𝘰𝘶𝘭𝘥𝘯'𝘵 say to people who are suicidal.⁠ 🚫⁠

Photos & caption by @mentalhealthceo

P.S. Save this post to your story as a reminder when you need it!⁠

Photo by RegenHealth on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2021 "I understand/ know how you feel." No, you don't. @mentalhealthceo'.

Photo by RegenHealth on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2021 "Other people have it worse. You have a roof over your head, food, water.. ...yet you are still suicidal?" This is highly insensitive and invalidates their struggles. @mentalhealthceo'.

Photo by RegenHealth on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2021 "Think about how your family/ friends would feel if you died." This causes more pain to the person. Please be very careful with this. @mentalhealthceo'.

Photo by RegenHealth on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2021 "Think about how I would feel if you died." Same with this phrase. Please be extremely cautious about this. @mentalhealthceo'.

Photo by RegenHealth on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2021 "Don't be selfish." It is a myth and a falsehood that suicide is selfish. It's a symptom of a mental illness. @mentalhealthceo'.
Photo by RegenHealth on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2021 Tasteless jokes. There's a time and a place for humor. This is not one of them. @mentalhealthceo'.

Photo by RegenHealth on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2021 Here's an alternative phrase to say: "I may never understand how you feel, but I will be with you all the way." Then, give them all the support you can give, together with active listening without judging them and invalidating their struggles. @mentalhealthceo'.

Photo by RegenHealth on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Most people clam up and don't know how to respond when a suicidal person opens up to them, which is why they make these mistakes. I wouldn't say it's their fault entirely-- they weren't trained, after all However, there's a right and a wrong way to respond to suicidal people. Please know the difference. Save this post as a reminder!'.

node.text:
Who can relate?⁣
🎨 @brushandbarley⁣
Photo by @health_anxiety⁣
⁠⁣
Anyone else with 30 unread messages because avoiding reading it means the pressure of replying and answering is less? 😅 sometimes I find myself turning my phone upside down and cringing when I hear it vibrate after I text something like having to say no, or backing out of a plan, or scheduling stuff or just anything 🤷🏼‍♀️ ya feel???⁣
Sometimes for me communicating feels like A LOT I put so much pressure on it and so much energy into making sure I say things “right”. It always feels like when my day is already super overwhelming is when the texts feel amplified overwhelming too.⁣
It’s okay to wait to reply, it’s okay to say no, it’s okay to say hey I’m struggling, it’s okay to not be okay 🤍⁣
⁣
🗣❤️ Tag a friend too, lets spread some easy therapy.⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RegenHealth on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'WAYS TO BOOST SEROTONIN eMAISIESGHOST GO FOR LONG WALKS OUTSIDE MEDS ENJOY SOME SUN EXPRESS GRATITUDE MEDITATE EAT SOME MOOD FOODS SUPPLEMENTS EXERCISE'.

node.text:
this pandemic has really done a number on my mental health (i’m sure many of you can relate). i’m surviving, but i don’t really feel like i’m thriving. it’s really important for me to continuously find ways to help boost my general energy and mood as it can help to keep me out of dark headspaces. there really are so many things you can do to increase your serotonin levels. i find myself creating checklists of what i can personally do daily. it usually helps on most days, but on the days it doesn’t, i just succumb to my heavier moods. i feel the feelings and ride out the day (or days).
it’s also important to note that in a lot of cases simple things like a walk or “mood foods” is not enough to help stabilize a mood. so, however, you get your serotonin (naturally or store-bought) is OKAY 🖤 we’re just human beings doing our best.
Photo and caption by @maisiesghost

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RegenHealth on July 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Joshua Fletcher @_AnxietyJosh Most panic attacks are not like they are on TV. They are mostly unnoticeable by others, because we can 'freeze' in fear. Our thoughts race, the heart rate increases, alongside a sense of doom and detachment. This is the most common panic attack, not rolling around screaming. @ANXIETY JOSH'.

node.text:
Often why it is so hard to explain to others who haven’t had a panic attack what it is like!
@anxietyjosh
